The tilde (/ ˈtɪldeɪ, -di, -də, ˈtɪld/)  ˜ ma ọ bụ ~, bụ grapheme nwere ọtụtụ ojiji
Aha agwa ahụ sitere na Spanish na Portuguese bata na bekee, nke n'aka nke ya sitere na Latin titulus, nke pụtara "aha" ma ọ bụ "edemede"
na Nchikota na a isi leta;  mana maka ebumnuche akụkọ ihe mere eme, a na-ejikwa ya n'ụdị kwụ ọtọ n'ime ọnọdụ dị iche iche.
Edeburu tilde ahụ n'elu mkpụrụedemede ewepụrụ ma ọ bụ ọtụtụ mkpụrụedemede dị ka mkpirisi edemede, ma ọ bụ "akara nkwusioru" na "akara nkwekọrịta", gosiri dị ka ahịrị kwụ ọtọ mgbe ejiri ya na isi
Ya mere, a na-akpọkarị okwu Anno Domini a na-akpọkarị Ao Dñi, nke nwere ọdụ elu nwere akara nkwusioru n'elu "n"
Ụdị akara ahụ nwere ike ịpụta nkwụsị nke otu mkpụrụedemede ma ọ bụ ọtụtụ mkpụrụedemede
Nke a zọpụtara n'efu nke ọrụ odeakwụkwọ na ọnụ ahịa vellum na ink
Edebere akwụkwọ ikike European Medieval na Latịn bụ n'ụzọ dị ukwuu mejupụtara okwu mkpirisi dị otú ahụ nwere akara nkwusioru na mbiri ndị ọzọ;  naanị okwu ndị a na-adịghị ahụkebe ka e nyere n'uju.
